<TITLE> Govt mulling crop insurance for farmers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 15 (bdnews24.com)The finance minister on Friday said the government was mulling over introducing crop insurance to protect farmers from crop damages. "Decision on how it can be implemented will be taken through discussions with all stakeholders," A M A Muhith said at a programme named 'Farmer's Budget 2009'. "Its easy to introduce poultry or fisheries insurance but complicated to introduce crop insurance as farmers produce a varieties of crops," he said. Private television Channel-i organised the programme where its authorities presented a set of recommendations ahead of the next budget. Muhith responded positively to a call to impose import duty on varieties of jujube/plum and strawberry to encourage local production. "Imposition of seasonal import duty can be given a thought considering the local producers of these fruits." "We think about a lot of good things but the implementation of those become impossible due to rules and regulations and corruption." Channel-i director Shaikh Siraj presented the recommendations of the Farmer's Budge 2009 gathered from farmers of two districts. bd
